Title: Counterfactuals, Control, and Causation: Why Knowledgable People Get Blamed More
Description: Project about how an actor's knowledge affects judgments about their causation.  Implications for mens rea and blame judgments.  Other Authors: Barbara Spellman, Elizabeth Tenney, Chris Holland
Contributors: Elizabeth Gilbert, Bobbie Spellman
Tags: 

